# Weapons & player

## When adding a new weapon, you must

1. Define stats on `WeaponData` (`weapons/data/weapon_data.gd`) via `.tres` or a catalog entry in `weapons/catalogs/`.
2. Register it in the correct catalog (`ranged_weapon_catalog.gd`, `melee_weapon_catalog.gd`, or `magic_weapon_catalog.gd`) so `WeaponSelectMenu` can offer it.
3. Ensure `weapon_id` (or unique `resource_path`) is unique — duplicate keys break `Player.has_weapon` / menu filtering.
4. Verify `weapons/core/gun.gd` already handles the weapon’s `weapon_type` / `weapon_subtype` / `magic_attack_style` / `ranged_attack_style`; if not, extend `gun.gd` and the required projectile/melee scene in the same change.
5. If the weapon spawns a new projectile scene, add `pool_reset` / `pool_on_acquire` and end with `PoolUtil.release_node` (spawn via `gun.gd` `_spawn_from_pool`).

Skipping step 2 makes the weapon invisible in level-up selection.

## Must not

- Do not equip weapons by instancing `gun.tscn` outside `Player.add_weapon()`.
- Do not add duplicate weapons to `_owned_weapons` (respect `get_unique_key()`).
- Do not break `Gun.equip_weapon` → `arrange_slot` orbit layout on `%Weapons`.

## Must (player / game flow)

- Level-up must go through `Player.leveled_up` → `Game.show_weapon_select` → `Game.on_weapon_chosen` → `add_weapon.call_deferred`.
- While weapon select is open, do not unpause or start spawn timer via side paths.
- `get_tree().paused = true` during weapon select and game over; resume only through `resume_game()` / `on_weapon_chosen` / restart.

## Damage API

- Use `Mob.take_damage` / `Mob.apply_weapon_damage` / `Mob.take_magic_damage` — do not write ad-hoc `health -=` on mobs from new weapon code.
- Use `FloatingDamageText` spawn helpers for new damage types; do not invent parallel floating text systems.

## When editing `ui/weapon_select_menu.gd`

- You must keep weapon pools sourced from the three catalogs; do not hardcode weapon lists only in the scene without updating catalogs.
- `CHOICE_COUNT` and `_buttons` node paths must stay consistent with `survivors_game.tscn` button names (`ContentHBox/ChoicesVBox/*`, `ContentHBox/DetailPanel/.../DetailLabel`).
- Weapon detail text must come from `WeaponData.build_select_tooltip_bbcode()`; do not duplicate stat formatting in the menu script.

## When editing weapon select tooltip text

- Update `WeaponData.build_select_tooltip_bbcode()` (and `_effect_ko()` if needed) when adding stats or special rules that players should see before picking a weapon.
- Throwing weapons must use `throw_range` for displayed range; melee uses `get_melee_range()`; other ranged/magic projectiles use `get_projectile_range()`.

## When touching catalogs

- After changing catalog cache build logic, you must ensure new weapons appear in `_get_all_weapons()` used by `present_random_choices`.
